author: James Ramage
title: Dollar Ticks Up on Monetary Policy Expectations
text:
The dollar edged higher against the euro and the yen Monday as investors expect the Federal Reserve will raise interest rates before central banks in the eurozone and Japan.
The dollar rose 0.2% against the common currency, as one euro bought $1.1321, the lowest against the greenback in more than a week. The dollar ticked up 0.1% versus the yen...
